dct_title_s: Chart of part of the South Sea shewing the tracts & discoveries made by His Majestys ships Dolphin
dct_description_sm: engrav'd by W. Whitchurch, Pleasant Row Islington.
Coordinates approximate and based on Greenwich meridian.
From Hawkesworth's, An account of the voyages undertaken ... in the southern hemisphere ..., London : W. Strahan & T. Cadell, 1773.
Map of South Pacific showing tracks of Wallis Carteret, Mouat and Cook.
